<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="1967" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1157,142,306]" box="[160,276,142,167]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1157,142,306]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">
Surstylus subbasally with irregular 1 row of ca. 6 somewhat thickened setae along inner margin, distally with two prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[615,728,212,236]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(b)); aedeagus erect and broadened, acute apically, its medial part sligtly spinulose and with a pair of thorn-like processes, one sheaf of setulae on submedial portion per side (
<figureCitation box="[763,870,282,306]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(c)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="1967" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,353,620]" box="[160,294,353,378]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,353,378]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,353,620]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">
Body colour had been almost lost, because preservation in 70% ethanol for long time. Male terminalia: Epandrium slightly prominent on posterolateral corners, with pubescence and dense setae (
<figureCitation box="[430,536,458,482]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(a)). Cercus lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[902,1008,458,482]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(a)). Surstylus basally with a few small setae, submedially curved, distally with ca. 12 long setae except prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[310,424,527,551]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(b)). Hypandrium with one pair of large flaps anteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[167,280,561,585]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(c)). Parameres slender, fused basally, with ca. 7–8 sensilla (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1115,561,585]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(c)). Gonopods low-reaching, fused with each other (
<figureCitation box="[713,821,596,620]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1613,1636]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-151@24.[163,1153,965,1582]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Stegana (Oxyphortica) spinosa Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c) hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182887/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1967">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(c)).
</paragraph>
